# Concurrent-session safety

Canonical protocol: `/Users/the1finix/Documents/GitHub/brain-box/agents/concurrent-session-safety.md`.

This repo, and its research sibling `finance-research-experiments`, can
have more than one Cursor session open at once — this actually happened
on 2026-07-01, when a research-pipeline-sweep session raced an unrelated
M001 session on shared files in `finance-research-experiments`. Git does
not protect you here: no branch divergence, just a race on one working
tree, and `git commit` can silently discard the other session's edits.

Before editing or committing `ai_context.md`, `docs/CHECKPOINT.md`, or
any other file you didn't create earlier in this same session:

1. Re-read it fresh immediately before editing.
2. Prefer additive edits over full rewrites.
3. Never `git add -A` / `git add .` — stage explicit paths only.
4. Before committing, run `git diff --cached <file>` and confirm every
   line is yours; unrecognized content means another session is active
   — stop and reconcile by hand, don't overwrite.
5. Commit in small units rather than one end-of-session batch.

See also: `/Users/the1finix/Documents/GitHub/brain-box/.cursor/rules/concurrent-session-safety.mdc`
